@table @asis
@item name:
area-tag
@item file:
filename(s) for this area without extension; 
should be the area-tag (as far as possible)
if file == Passthrough then [<msgBase>] is skipped and msgarea is
set as an passthrough area
@item msgbase:
*.msg is standard. Write Squish for an Squish-msgbase
@item LinkAKA:
aka's of up- and down links
@end table

Options:

@table @asis
@item -l @{<group>@}
read/write access for group
@item -r @{<group>@}
read access for group 
@item -w @{<group>@}
write access for group
if a group name is an unsignedInteger, it is
interpreted as level, access rights are
granted for links with equal or higher level
@item -p <integer>
purge after n days, 
@item -m <integer>
